This paper deals with the application of Deep Neural Networks (DNNs) and proposes a novel approach for reducing the number of trainable parameters and increasing their physical interpretability. This work is relevant to the fields of machine learning, neural networks, and data science, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper deals with the development of a new framework for DNNs. The second most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper focuses on the application of DNNs and proposes a new approach for their optimization. The third most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), as the paper validates the proposed framework on benchmark datasets for image classification. The fourth most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper deals with the development of a new approach for optimizing DNNs. The fifth most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper proposes a new approach for reducing the number of parameters in DNNs, which is relevant to the field of data science.
